        ],
        [
          544.6207885742188,
          613.333984375
        ],
        [
          544.6207885742188,
          709.5528793334961
        ],
        [
          303.310546875,
          709.5528793334961
        ]
      ],
      "text": "The poor aqueous solubility of xanthone (XAN) and of many of its derivatives such as 3-methoxyxanthone (3-MeOXAN) ( Fig. 1) is a major drawback not only for their use in the therapy but even for the in vitro assessment of their biological activity. One approach to overcome the difficulty of administration of poorly water-soluble compounds is their incorporation in polymeric nanocarriers [10–12] . Depending on the processing conditions, either",
      "section_hierarchy": {
        "2": "/page/0/SectionHeader/15"
      }
    },
